           try {
               System.out.println("Accessing object's method");
               // Call a method on myObject
           } catch (NullPointerException e) {
               System.err.println("Caught NullPointerException: " + e.getMessage());
           }
       }
   }
   ```

4. **Use `instanceof`:**  Check if an object is of a specific class before accessing its members:
   ```java
